oc:kn_1c488073 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When synthesizing context into the prep brief" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not skip the discovery questions section even when account history is rich — gaps always exist in understanding the current situation, priorities, and decision process" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Overconfidence in existing account knowledge leads to missed qualification signals and unpreparedness for new developments" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_2a6b1a6d a oc:FallbackStrategy,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When connectors are unavailable" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When no connectors are available, fall back to direct user questions for company name, meeting type, attendees, and any context they can paste — then rely on web research to fill gaps" ;
    oc:hasRationale "The skill must provide value standalone; connectors enhance but are not required" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_89c48fe3 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When gathering input from user" ;
    oc:directiveContent "More context yields better prep — always accept whatever the user provides (notes, emails, partial info) and work with it rather than insisting on completeness" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Users often have fragmented context; maximizing input utilization produces significantly better prep briefs" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_9aeaca25 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating the prep brief agenda section" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Tailor agenda and discovery questions to meeting type: discovery calls emphasize questions over talking, demos focus on use-case relevance, negotiations prioritize objection handling, check-ins review wins and surface expansion opportunities" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Generic agendas fail because each meeting type has distinct goals and conversation dynamics" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_9ca03aeb a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting context gathering" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Company or contact name and meeting type are required inputs; the skill cannot proceed without them" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without identifying the company and meeting purpose, research and agenda generation cannot be meaningfully targeted" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_d074002d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PerformanceProfile ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning execution time expectations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Connector-based gathering involves 5 parallel data pulls (Calendar, CRM, Email, Chat, Transcripts); web research involves 5 search queries — total execution time scales with slowest connector response" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Understanding the parallel data collection pattern helps manage user expectations on wait time" ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_ea87438c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "During the research supplement phase" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always run web research (company news, funding, leadership changes, industry trends, attendee backgrounds) regardless of connector availability — it supplements but does not replace connected data" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Web research fills gaps that internal systems cannot provide, especially for recent developments and attendee backgrounds" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

